<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 10:10PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
south central Campbell, northeastern Pittsylvania and northwestern
Halifax Counties through 1045 PM EDT...
At 1010 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brookneal, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cody...
Leda...
Straightstone...
Long Island...
and Hodges.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
